.name
SafeMalloc
.author
Bjorn Benson
modifications by Fred Fish 
.description
Ever have a program that corrupts it's own memory? Well, this little gem
can help you find the problem in a hurry.  Acts as an interface between
your program and the real malloc, checking for overrun, underrun, and
duplicate freeing of malloc'd space.  
